Note: Advanced Temporal Reasoning System for AI Agents
Note: Implements temporal logic, time-based inference, event sequences,
Note: temporal constraints, planning, and temporal knowledge representation

Note: Core temporal types
Type called "TimePoint":
    timestamp as String  Note: ISO 8601 format
    granularity as String  Note: "instant", "second", "minute", "hour", "day", "month", "year"
    uncertainty as Float  Note: Temporal uncertainty measure
    timezone as String
    calendar_system as String
    metadata as Dictionary

Type called "TimeInterval":
    start_time as TimePoint
    end_time as TimePoint
    duration as Float  Note: In seconds
    interval_type as String  Note: "open", "closed", "half_open_left", "half_open_right"
    certainty as Float
    source as String

Type called "TemporalRelation":
    relation_type as String  Note: "before", "after", "during", "overlaps", "meets", "starts", "finishes", "equals"
    entity1 as String
    entity2 as String
    confidence as Float
    temporal_distance as Float  Note: Optional quantitative measure
    context as Dictionary

Type called "TemporalEvent":
    event_id as String
    event_type as String
    time_point as TimePoint
    duration as TimeInterval
    participants as List[String]
    properties as Dictionary
    causal_links as List[String]  Note: Links to other events
    probability as Float
    certainty as Float

Type called "TemporalSequence":
    sequence_id as String
    events as List[TemporalEvent]
    temporal_constraints as List[TemporalConstraint]
    sequence_pattern as String
    probability as Float
    context as Dictionary

Type called "TemporalConstraint":
    constraint_id as String
    constraint_type as String  Note: "precedence", "simultaneity", "duration", "periodicity"
    involved_events as List[String]
    parameters as Dictionary  Note: Specific constraint parameters
    strength as Float  Note: How hard/soft the constraint is
    violation_penalty as Float

Type called "TemporalLogic":
    formula_type as String  Note: "LTL", "CTL", "MTL", "TCTL"
    temporal_operators as List[String]  Note: "eventually", "always", "until", "next", "since"
    propositions as List[String]
    formula_string as String
    truth_value as String  Note: "true", "false", "unknown", "undefined"
    satisfaction_trace as List[Dictionary]

Type called "TemporalKnowledgeBase":
    time_points as List[TimePoint]
    intervals as List[TimeInterval]
    events as List[TemporalEvent]
    relations as List[TemporalRelation]
    sequences as List[TemporalSequence]
    constraints as List[TemporalConstraint]
    temporal_ontology as Dictionary
    inference_rules as List[Dictionary]

Type called "TemporalReasoner":
    knowledge_base as TemporalKnowledgeBase
    reasoning_mode as String  Note: "qualitative", "quantitative", "hybrid"
    temporal_logic_system as String
    constraint_solver as String
    uncertainty_handling as String
    performance_metrics as Dictionary

Note: Temporal relationship inference
Process called "infer_temporal_relations" that takes reasoner as TemporalReasoner and events as List[TemporalEvent] returns List[TemporalRelation]:
    Let relations be empty list
    Let knowledge_base be reasoner with field knowledge_base
    
    Note: Compare all pairs of events
    For i from 0 to length of events minus 1:
        For j from i plus 1 to length of events minus 1:
            Let event1 be events with index i
            Let event2 be events with index j
            
            Let direct_relation be compute_direct_temporal_relation with event1 and event2
            If direct_relation is not equal to null:
                Add direct_relation to relations
            
            Note: Infer indirect relations through transitivity
            Let indirect_relations be infer_transitive_relations with event1 and event2 and knowledge_base
            Add all indirect_relations to relations
    
    Note: Apply temporal reasoning rules
    Let inferred_relations be apply_temporal_inference_rules with relations and knowledge_base
    Add all inferred_relations to relations
    
    Note: Remove contradictions and redundancies
    Let consistent_relations be resolve_temporal_contradictions with relations
    
    Return consistent_relations

Process called "compute_direct_temporal_relation" that takes event1 as TemporalEvent and event2 as TemporalEvent returns TemporalRelation:
    Let time1 be event1 with field time_point
    Let duration1 be event1 with field duration
    Let time2 be event2 with field time_point
    Let duration2 be event2 with field duration
    
    Note: Convert to comparable timestamps
    Let start1 be parse_timestamp with time1 with field timestamp
    Let end1 be start1 plus duration1 with field duration
    Let start2 be parse_timestamp with time2 with field timestamp
    Let end2 be start2 plus duration2 with field duration
    
    Let relation be create_temporal_relation_structure
    Set relation with field entity1 to event1 with field event_id
    Set relation with field entity2 to event2 with field event_id
    
    Note: Determine relationship type using Allen's interval algebra
    If end1 is less than start2:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "before"
        Set relation with field temporal_distance to start2 minus end1
    
    If start1 is greater than end2:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "after"
        Set relation with field temporal_distance to start1 minus end2
    
    If start1 is less than start2 and end1 is greater than start2 and end1 is less than end2:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "overlaps"
    
    If start2 is less than start1 and end2 is greater than start1 and end2 is less than end1:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "overlapped_by"
    
    If start1 is less than or equal to start2 and end1 is greater than or equal to end2:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "contains"
    
    If start2 is less than or equal to start1 and end2 is greater than or equal to end1:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "during"
    
    If start1 is equal to start2 and end1 is equal to end2:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "equals"
    
    If end1 is equal to start2:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "meets"
    
    If end2 is equal to start1:
        Set relation with field relation_type to "met_by"
    
    Note: Calculate confidence based on temporal certainty
    Let certainty1 be time1 with field uncertainty
    Let certainty2 be time2 with field uncertainty
    Set relation with field confidence to (certainty1 plus certainty2) divided by 2.0
    
    Return relation

Process called "infer_transitive_relations" that takes event1 as TemporalEvent and event2 as TemporalEvent and knowledge_base as TemporalKnowledgeBase returns List[TemporalRelation]:
    Let transitive_relations be empty list
    Let existing_relations be knowledge_base with field relations
    
    Note: Find intermediate events
    For each relation1 in existing_relations:
        If relation1 with field entity1 is equal to event1 with field event_id:
            Let intermediate_event be relation1 with field entity2
            
            Note: Look for relation from intermediate to event2
            For each relation2 in existing_relations:
                If relation2 with field entity1 is equal to intermediate_event and relation2 with field entity2 is equal to event2 with field event_id:
                    Let transitive_relation be compute_transitive_relation with relation1 and relation2
                    If transitive_relation is not equal to null:
                        Add transitive_relation to transitive_relations
    
    Return transitive_relations

Process called "compute_transitive_relation" that takes relation1 as TemporalRelation and relation2 as TemporalRelation returns TemporalRelation:
    Let type1 be relation1 with field relation_type
    Let type2 be relation2 with field relation_type
    Let transitive_type be null
    
    Note: Allen's interval algebra transitivity table
    If type1 is equal to "before" and type2 is equal to "before":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    If type1 is equal to "before" and type2 is equal to "meets":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    If type1 is equal to "before" and type2 is equal to "overlaps":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    If type1 is equal to "before" and type2 is equal to "starts":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    If type1 is equal to "before" and type2 is equal to "during":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    If type1 is equal to "meets" and type2 is equal to "before":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    If type1 is equal to "meets" and type2 is equal to "meets":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    If type1 is equal to "overlaps" and type2 is equal to "before":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    If type1 is equal to "during" and type2 is equal to "before":
        Set transitive_type to "before"
    
    Note: Add more transitivity rules...
    
    If transitive_type is not equal to null:
        Let transitive_relation be create_temporal_relation_structure
        Set transitive_relation with field entity1 to relation1 with field entity1
        Set transitive_relation with field entity2 to relation2 with field entity2
        Set transitive_relation with field relation_type to transitive_type
        Set transitive_relation with field confidence to minimum of (relation1 with field confidence) and (relation2 with field confidence)
        Return transitive_relation
    
    Return null

Note: Temporal constraint satisfaction
Process called "solve_temporal_constraints" that takes constraints as List[TemporalConstraint] and events as List[TemporalEvent] returns Dictionary:
    Let constraint_network be build_constraint_network with constraints and events
    Let solution be solve_csp_network with constraint_network
    
    If solution with field satisfiable is equal to true:
        Let temporal_assignment be extract_temporal_assignment with solution and events
        Let consistency_score be calculate_consistency_score with temporal_assignment and constraints
        
        Return dictionary with keys "satisfiable", "assignment", "consistency_score", "violated_constraints":
            "satisfiable" maps to true
            "assignment" maps to temporal_assignment
            "consistency_score" maps to consistency_score
            "violated_constraints" maps to empty list
    Otherwise:
        Let relaxed_solution be solve_with_relaxation with constraint_network and constraints
        Return relaxed_solution

Process called "build_constraint_network" that takes constraints as List[TemporalConstraint] and events as List[TemporalEvent] returns Dictionary:
    Let network be empty dictionary
    Let variables be empty list
    Let domains be empty dictionary
    Let constraint_graph be empty dictionary
    
    Note: Create variables for event start and end times
    For each event in events:
        Let start_var be event with field event_id Joined with "_start"
        Let end_var be event with field event_id Joined with "_end"
        Add start_var to variables
        Add end_var to variables
        
        Note: Define domains based on event time constraints
        Let time_domain be create_time_domain with event
        Set domains with key start_var to time_domain
        Set domains with key end_var to time_domain
    
    Note: Add constraints to network
    For each constraint in constraints:
        Let constraint_type be constraint with field constraint_type
        Let involved_events be constraint with field involved_events
        
        If constraint_type is equal to "precedence":
            Add precedence constraint to constraint_graph with involved_events
        
        If constraint_type is equal to "simultaneity":
            Add simultaneity constraint to constraint_graph with involved_events
        
        If constraint_type is equal to "duration":
            Add duration constraint to constraint_graph with involved_events and constraint with field parameters
        
        If constraint_type is equal to "periodicity":
            Add periodicity constraint to constraint_graph with involved_events and constraint with field parameters
    
    Set network with key "variables" to variables
    Set network with key "domains" to domains
    Set network with key "constraints" to constraint_graph
    
    Return network

Process called "solve_csp_network" that takes network as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let variables be network with key "variables"
    Let domains be network with key "domains"
    Let constraints be network with key "constraints"
    
    Note: Use backtracking search with constraint propagation
    Let assignment be empty dictionary
    Let solution be backtrack_search with assignment and variables and domains and constraints
    
    Return solution

Process called "backtrack_search" that takes assignment as Dictionary and variables as List[String] and domains as Dictionary and constraints as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Note: Check if assignment is complete
    If length of assignment is equal to length of variables:
        Return dictionary with keys "satisfiable", "assignment":
            "satisfiable" maps to true
            "assignment" maps to assignment
    
    Note: Select unassigned variable
    Let unassigned_var be select_unassigned_variable with assignment and variables
    Let variable_domain be domains with key unassigned_var
    
    Note: Try each value in domain
    For each value in variable_domain:
        Note: Check consistency with existing assignment
        If is_consistent with unassigned_var and value and assignment and constraints:
            Note: Make assignment
            Set assignment with key unassigned_var to value
            
            Note: Propagate constraints
            Let propagated_domains be propagate_constraints with assignment and domains and constraints
            
            Note: Recursive call
            Let result be backtrack_search with assignment and variables and propagated_domains and constraints
            If result with field satisfiable is equal to true:
                Return result
            
            Note: Backtrack
            Remove unassigned_var from assignment
    
    Return dictionary with keys "satisfiable", "assignment":
        "satisfiable" maps to false
        "assignment" maps to null

Note: Temporal logic evaluation
Process called "evaluate_temporal_logic_formula" that takes formula as TemporalLogic and trace as List[Dictionary] and reasoner as TemporalReasoner returns Dictionary:
    Let formula_type be formula with field formula_type
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    If formula_type is equal to "LTL":
        Set result to evaluate_ltl_formula with formula and trace
    
    If formula_type is equal to "CTL":
        Set result to evaluate_ctl_formula with formula and trace
    
    If formula_type is equal to "MTL":
        Set result to evaluate_mtl_formula with formula and trace
    
    If formula_type is equal to "TCTL":
        Set result to evaluate_tctl_formula with formula and trace
    
    Note: Add satisfaction trace
    Set result with key "satisfaction_trace" to generate_satisfaction_trace with formula and trace and result
    Set result with key "evaluation_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    
    Return result

Process called "evaluate_ltl_formula" that takes formula as TemporalLogic and trace as List[Dictionary] returns Dictionary:
    Let formula_string be formula with field formula_string
    Let temporal_operators be formula with field temporal_operators
    Let propositions be formula with field propositions
    
    Note: Parse and evaluate LTL formula
    Let parsed_formula be parse_ltl_formula with formula_string
    Let evaluation_result be evaluate_ltl_on_trace with parsed_formula and trace
    
    Return dictionary with keys "truth_value", "satisfaction_points", "violation_points", "evaluation_details":
        "truth_value" maps to evaluation_result with field truth_value
        "satisfaction_points" maps to evaluation_result with field satisfaction_points
        "violation_points" maps to evaluation_result with field violation_points
        "evaluation_details" maps to evaluation_result with field details

Process called "evaluate_ltl_on_trace" that takes parsed_formula as Dictionary and trace as List[Dictionary] returns Dictionary:
    Let trace_length be length of trace
    Let satisfaction_points be empty list
    Let violation_points be empty list
    Let truth_value be "unknown"
    
    Note: Evaluate formula at each time point in trace
    For index from 0 to trace_length minus 1:
        Let current_state be trace with index index
        Let evaluation_at_point be evaluate_ltl_at_point with parsed_formula and trace and index
        
        If evaluation_at_point with field satisfied is equal to true:
            Add index to satisfaction_points
        Otherwise:
            Add index to violation_points
    
    Note: Determine overall truth value
    If length of violation_points is equal to 0:
        Set truth_value to "true"
    Otherwise if length of satisfaction_points is greater than 0:
        Set truth_value to "partially_satisfied"
    Otherwise:
        Set truth_value to "false"
    
    Return dictionary with keys "truth_value", "satisfaction_points", "violation_points", "details":
        "truth_value" maps to truth_value
        "satisfaction_points" maps to satisfaction_points
        "violation_points" maps to violation_points
        "details" maps to create_evaluation_details with parsed_formula and trace

Note: Temporal planning and prediction
Process called "perform_temporal_planning" that takes goal_state as Dictionary and initial_state as Dictionary and actions as List[Dictionary] and temporal_constraints as List[TemporalConstraint] returns Dictionary:
    Let planner be create_temporal_planner with actions and temporal_constraints
    Let plan be search_for_temporal_plan with planner and initial_state and goal_state
    
    If plan with field found is equal to true:
        Let validated_plan be validate_temporal_plan with plan and temporal_constraints
        Let optimized_plan be optimize_temporal_plan with validated_plan
        
        Return dictionary with keys "success", "plan", "makespan", "resource_usage", "robustness":
            "success" maps to true
            "plan" maps to optimized_plan with field actions
            "makespan" maps to optimized_plan with field total_time
            "resource_usage" maps to optimized_plan with field resources
            "robustness" maps to calculate_plan_robustness with optimized_plan
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary with keys "success", "failure_reason", "partial_plan":
            "success" maps to false
            "failure_reason" maps to plan with field failure_reason
            "partial_plan" maps to plan with field partial_solution

Process called "predict_temporal_sequences" that takes historical_events as List[TemporalEvent] and prediction_horizon as Float and reasoner as TemporalReasoner returns List[TemporalSequence]:
    Let sequence_patterns be extract_temporal_patterns with historical_events
    Let predictions be empty list
    
    For each pattern in sequence_patterns:
        Let pattern_strength be calculate_pattern_strength with pattern and historical_events
        If pattern_strength is greater than 0.7:  Note: Strong pattern threshold
            Let predicted_sequence be project_pattern_forward with pattern and prediction_horizon
            Set predicted_sequence with field probability to pattern_strength
            Add predicted_sequence to predictions
    
    Note: Apply temporal reasoning to refine predictions
    Let refined_predictions be apply_temporal_constraints_to_predictions with predictions and reasoner
    
    Note: Rank predictions by likelihood and confidence
    Let ranked_predictions be rank_predictions_by_likelihood with refined_predictions
    
    Return ranked_predictions

Process called "extract_temporal_patterns" that takes events as List[TemporalEvent] returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let patterns be empty list
    Let event_sequences be group_events_by_context with events
    
    For each sequence in event_sequences:
        Note: Look for recurring patterns
        Let recurring_patterns be find_recurring_subsequences with sequence
        Add all recurring_patterns to patterns
        
        Note: Look for causal patterns
        Let causal_patterns be identify_causal_patterns with sequence
        Add all causal_patterns to patterns
        
        Note: Look for periodic patterns
        Let periodic_patterns be detect_periodic_patterns with sequence
        Add all periodic_patterns to patterns
    
    Note: Filter and consolidate patterns
    Let significant_patterns be filter_significant_patterns with patterns
    
    Return significant_patterns

Note: Temporal uncertainty and fuzzy time
Process called "handle_temporal_uncertainty" that takes temporal_facts as List[Dictionary] and uncertainty_model as String returns Dictionary:
    Let uncertain_intervals be empty list
    Let confidence_scores be empty dictionary
    
    For each fact in temporal_facts:
        If fact contains key "temporal_uncertainty":
            Let uncertainty be fact with key "temporal_uncertainty"
            Let uncertain_interval be create_uncertain_interval with fact and uncertainty and uncertainty_model
            Add uncertain_interval to uncertain_intervals
            
            Let confidence be calculate_temporal_confidence with fact and uncertainty_model
            Set confidence_scores with key (fact with key "id") to confidence
    
    Note: Propagate uncertainty through temporal reasoning
    Let propagated_uncertainty be propagate_temporal_uncertainty with uncertain_intervals and confidence_scores
    
    Return dictionary with keys "uncertain_intervals", "confidence_scores", "propagated_uncertainty":
        "uncertain_intervals" maps to uncertain_intervals
        "confidence_scores" maps to confidence_scores
        "propagated_uncertainty" maps to propagated_uncertainty

Process called "create_uncertain_interval" that takes fact as Dictionary and uncertainty as Float and model as String returns Dictionary:
    Let base_time be fact with key "timestamp"
    Let parsed_time be parse_timestamp with base_time
    
    If model is equal to "gaussian":
        Let std_dev be uncertainty times 1.96  Note: 95% confidence interval
        Let lower_bound be parsed_time minus std_dev
        Let upper_bound be parsed_time plus std_dev
        
        Return dictionary with keys "type", "lower_bound", "upper_bound", "mean", "std_dev":
            "type" maps to "gaussian_interval"
            "lower_bound" maps to lower_bound
            "upper_bound" maps to upper_bound
            "mean" maps to parsed_time
            "std_dev" maps to std_dev
    
    If model is equal to "uniform":
        Let half_range be uncertainty
        Let lower_bound be parsed_time minus half_range
        Let upper_bound be parsed_time plus half_range
        
        Return dictionary with keys "type", "lower_bound", "upper_bound":
            "type" maps to "uniform_interval"
            "lower_bound" maps to lower_bound
            "upper_bound" maps to upper_bound
    
    Return null

Note: Main temporal reasoning coordination
Process called "create_temporal_reasoner" that takes configuration as Dictionary returns TemporalReasoner:
    Let reasoner be create_temporal_reasoner_structure
    Let knowledge_base be create_empty_temporal_knowledge_base
    
    Set reasoner with field knowledge_base to knowledge_base
    Set reasoner with field reasoning_mode to configuration with key "reasoning_mode" or "hybrid"
    Set reasoner with field temporal_logic_system to configuration with key "logic_system" or "LTL"
    Set reasoner with field constraint_solver to configuration with key "constraint_solver" or "backtrack"
    Set reasoner with field uncertainty_handling to configuration with key "uncertainty_handling" or "gaussian"
    Set reasoner with field performance_metrics to empty dictionary
    
    Return reasoner

Process called "execute_temporal_reasoning" that takes reasoner as TemporalReasoner and query as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let query_type be query with key "type"
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    If query_type is equal to "relation_inference":
        Let events be query with key "events"
        Let inferred_relations be infer_temporal_relations with reasoner and events
        Set result with key "relations" to inferred_relations
    
    If query_type is equal to "constraint_satisfaction":
        Let constraints be query with key "constraints"
        Let events be query with key "events"
        Let solution be solve_temporal_constraints with constraints and events
        Set result to solution
    
    If query_type is equal to "logic_evaluation":
        Let formula be query with key "formula"
        Let trace be query with key "trace"
        Let evaluation be evaluate_temporal_logic_formula with formula and trace and reasoner
        Set result to evaluation
    
    If query_type is equal to "temporal_planning":
        Let goal_state be query with key "goal_state"
        Let initial_state be query with key "initial_state"
        Let actions be query with key "actions"
        Let constraints be query with key "constraints"
        Let plan be perform_temporal_planning with goal_state and initial_state and actions and constraints
        Set result to plan
    
    If query_type is equal to "sequence_prediction":
        Let historical_events be query with key "historical_events"
        Let prediction_horizon be query with key "prediction_horizon"
        Let predictions be predict_temporal_sequences with historical_events and prediction_horizon and reasoner
        Set result with key "predictions" to predictions
    
    If query_type is equal to "uncertainty_analysis":
        Let temporal_facts be query with key "temporal_facts"
        Let uncertainty_model be query with key "uncertainty_model"
        Let uncertainty_analysis be handle_temporal_uncertainty with temporal_facts and uncertainty_model
        Set result to uncertainty_analysis
    
    Note: Add metadata
    Set result with key "reasoning_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    Set result with key "reasoner_config" to extract_reasoner_config with reasoner
    
    Return result